    "In complete androgen insensitivity syndrome, a 46,XY individual has functioning testes (SRY present) that secrete anti-Mullerian hormone and testosterone. AMH from Sertoli cells regresses the Mullerian ducts, so there is no uterus, cervix, or upper vagina, hence the blind vaginal pouch. Because the androgen receptor is defective, target tissues cannot respond to androgens, so external genitalia are female and pubic/axillary hair is scant; peripheral aromatization of testosterone to estrogen drives breast development. The testes are typically intra-abdominal or inguinal.",
