    'MSK',
    'Gout Crystal Identification',
    "A 55-year-old man with hypertension presents with acute, exquisitely painful swelling and erythema of the first metatarsophalangeal joint that woke him at night. Joint aspiration under polarized light shows needle-shaped crystals that are yellow when aligned parallel to the compensator. Which crystal type is present?",
    "Monosodium urate crystals, which are needle-shaped and negatively birefringent",
