    'Career Skills',
    'Neuroscience',
    'Wallenberg Lateral Medullary Syndrome',
    "A 58-year-old man with atrial fibrillation suddenly develops vertigo, dysphagia, hoarseness, and loss of pain and temperature sensation on the left side of his face and the right side of his body. He has ptosis and miosis on the left. Occlusion of which artery best explains this syndrome?",
