    'Neuroscience',
    'Weber Midbrain Syndrome',
    "A 65-year-old hypertensive man develops a right eye that is deviated down and out with ptosis and a dilated pupil, together with left-sided weakness of the face, arm, and leg. Which lesion best explains these combined findings?",
