    "Weber syndrome is a medial midbrain stroke (paramedian branches of the posterior cerebral artery) that damages the exiting oculomotor (CN III) fibers and the cerebral peduncle. CN III involvement gives an ipsilateral down-and-out eye with ptosis and a dilated, poorly reactive pupil, while peduncle (corticospinal tract above its decussation) involvement gives contralateral hemiparesis of the face, arm, and leg. This crossed pattern, an ipsilateral cranial nerve palsy with contralateral hemiparesis, is the hallmark of a brainstem lesion.",
