    'Serotonin Syndrome vs NMS',
    "A 24-year-old started on an SSRI has tramadol added for pain. Within hours he develops agitation, diaphoresis, hyperthermia, tremor, and hyperreflexia with sustained clonus that is more pronounced in the lower extremities. Which is the most likely diagnosis, and what is the discriminating neuromuscular finding?",
    "Serotonin syndrome, discriminated by hyperreflexia and clonus",
