    'Huntington Disease Genetics',
    "A 40-year-old man develops involuntary, jerky, dance-like movements, irritability, and progressive cognitive decline. His father had a similar illness that began at age 45. MRI shows atrophy of the caudate nuclei. Which genetic mechanism underlies this disease and explains his earlier onset?",
    "An expanded CAG trinucleotide repeat in the huntingtin gene, with anticipation in paternal transmission",
