    "Huntington disease is an autosomal dominant neurodegenerative disorder caused by expansion of a CAG trinucleotide repeat in the huntingtin (HTT) gene on chromosome 4. It produces chorea, behavioral changes, and dementia, with caudate (and putamen) atrophy and loss of GABAergic neurons, leading to ex vacuo ventricular dilation. Longer repeats cause earlier onset, and anticipation, earlier and more severe disease in successive generations, is most pronounced with paternal transmission because of repeat instability during spermatogenesis.",
